  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening Institutional Capacity in STEM Education, Research and Innovation in Collaboration with Regional Networks and UNESCO Chairs and C2Cs</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The role played by STEM in achieving global goals as contained in UN Agenda 2030, AU Agenda 2063 and STISA-2024 is widely acknowledged. Many countries are therefore advocating for new STEM education and market responsive curriculum to accelerate Africa&apos;s aspiration for socio-economic transformation 2024. In this context, support to regional Networks of institutions and CoEs to enhance capacity in research, education and training, high skills development and innovation in STEM will create the critical mass of expertise needed to accelerate the socio-economic transformation of Africa. In collaboration with Education Sector, integrating innovative technologies in the teaching of STEM will help to develop in students 21st century skills that include creativity, innovation, problem solving.</narrative>
  </description>
